abstract: Luke Aikins becomes first person to skydive without parachute, falling from 25,000 feet into giant net.

headline.print_headline: A 25,000-Foot Free Fall, and Without a Parachute
headline.main: Skydiver Survives Jump From 25,000 Feet, and Without a Parachute

snippet: With a live television audience watching, Luke Aikins, a veteran jumper, drops into a net less than half the size of a football field in the California desert....
lead_paragraph: With a live television audience watching, Luke Aikins, a veteran jumper, drops into a net less than half the size of a football field in the California desert.
